 Bae U | Photo Instagram Instagram comedian Bae U has made a public apology following the sex-for-role allegations made against him. Over the weekend, popular gossip site GistLovers called out Bae U for allegedly refusing to pay a lady who claimed he promised to send her money after making explicit video calls with her. The gossip site alleges that the lady had shared explicit videos of Bae U asking that they post it since he had refused to pay her. Following these allegations, other victims of the comedian’s explicit demands sent messages to the site with proof. A noticeable detail in the screenshots shared is that the comedian insinuated that these ladies “freaky” him, a term which has recently be used to insinuate sexual activities in return for roles in his skits. Breaking the silence over these allegations, the comedian whose relationship with fellow comedian Mummy Wa has been made public took to Instagram to share his apology with his six hundred thousand Instagram followers. He said, “I am here because of those that love me, and I have let down. I have seen and received every stone thrown at me. I am human, and so are you all, so I am not here to blame anyone for what’s happening… anyone but myself.” “So I am here to say one or two things; I have been heartbroken and weak.” Bae U claimed that following GistLovers post; he began to get unsent messages. He continued, “One more thing I pray and hope that we can go back to making money off skits for people that think I’m funny and creative.” See the full video HERE:   A post shared by Isbae U (@isbae_u)